🦝 Trash Panda Module (Raccoon) — v1.0

Role

Selective scavenger and filter.

Lives at the boundary between:

* noise ↔ signal
* trash ↔ treasure

⸻

Core Function

Sort, strip, salvage, or discard incoming material

Where:

* Hermit Crab = reuse what’s already chosen
* Raccoon = decide what’s worth keeping in the first place

⸻

Behavior Loop

1. Scan
    * grab raw input (ideas, trends, data, noise)
2. Triage
    * classify into:
        * 🟢 keep (signal)
        * 🟡 salvage (partial value)
        * 🔴 discard (noise)
3. Strip Value
    * extract useful components from “salvage”
    * remove fluff, hype, excess
4. Route
    * keep → Money Bin (Seed/Signal)
    * salvage → Hermit Crab (refactor/reuse)
    * discard → garbage collection (Ammit / void)

⸻

Interfaces (Pantheon Integration)

* Hound
    → flags suspicious or interesting anomalies
    → Raccoon investigates further
* Mirror
    → tests if “signal” actually holds
    → prevents Raccoon from keeping shiny trash
* Hermit Crab
    → receives salvageable pieces
    → repurposes into usable forms
* Ammit (Garbage Collector)
    → final discard path
    → ensures clean deletion when needed
* Spider
    → only archives what passes Raccoon + Mirror

⸻

Heuristics (Decision Rules)

* If it only works in one context → salvage or discard
* If it survives translation → keep
* If it’s trendy but untested → salvage (strip + test)
* If it’s complex but low utility → discard
* If small but reusable → keep (high leverage)

⸻

Failure Modes (Watch This)

* Shiny object syndrome
    → keeping novelty over utility
* Over-filtering
    → throwing away seeds too early
* Hoarding salvage
    → becomes clutter if not passed to Hermit Crab

